@node "FAQ" Frequently asked Questions - Overview"

                           @{u}FAQ - Short Overview@{uu}

  This guide describes the most common problems which occured during new
  installation or usage. Before writing a Bug-Report, please look here in
   this document and check out if your problem is described here. If you
 don't find it, please report your problem to the adress listed @{"here" LINK FAQ_CENTER}!    

    The FAQ are diverted in two parts, so you should find the required 
    informations without any problems. If you have any suggestions or 
             other things to report, feel free to contact us!

                         @{"     FAQ ABOUT FAME     " LINK FAQ_FAME}
                         @{" FAQ ABOUT AMIEX & FAME " LINK FAQ_AMIEX}
@endnode

@REM ===========================================================================

@node "FAQ_FAME" "Frequently asked Questions about FAME"

@{b}Q:@{ub} After adding a new Door and starting it, FAME does not start the door, the
   cursor only wraps to the next line, and nothing more happens.

@{b}A:@{ub} Check out the "DoorType" in SystemEditor/Doors for the tool, maybe you
   have set the @{fg shine}FIM@{fg text} flag for an @{fg shine}AMIEX@{fg text} door etc. Always use the right door-
   type, or FAME won't be able to start the door. You may kick out the
   door which crashed by using the CloseButton/Close door option.
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} After adding a new door and trying to start it, FAME always displays
   the errormessage: '@{b}Can't find custom command!@{ub}'

@{b}A:@{ub} Check out the Path to the door in SystemEditor/Doors! It may contain
   the wrong path to the door.
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} I've placed some textfiles containing calls to cli-programs in the Node
   batches directories, but FAME won't execute them ! Also other Script-
   files are not executed by FAME.

@{b}A:@{ub} Check out the '@{fg shine}S@{fg text}' bit of all textfiles you want to execute in FAME ! If
   this is not set, FAME won't start them! Simply use the DOS-Command

                    @{fg shine}PROTECT <FILENAME> +S@{fg text}

   and everything is fine.
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} I want to use the resident feature of FAME, so I've inserted a new line
   to '@{b}FAME:SETTINGS/FAMESTART.BAT@{ub}':
                  
                    RESIDENT FAME:MODULES/MAINPART PURE

   But FAME won't use this feature, MainPart will be loaded into memory
   for each Node I have regardeless if I write the line above or not.

@{b}A:@{ub} If you want to run resident programs, you *MUST* remove all path
   information for those programs, so only the Filename remains. Go into
   SystemEditor/Node Datas and remove (for every Node you want to have
   MainPart resident) the Path FAME:Modules/, and so only the FileName
   'MAINPART' remains in the MainPart Location field. That's it!! You could
   also check out if the resident version is used by entering 'RESIDENT' in a
   DOS-prompt. This shows a list of all currently used resident Programs and
   contains also a counter which indicates how many times this program
   has been used.
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} Is it possible to @{b}use Paragon doors@{ub}, and what is the name of the Paragon
   port ?

@{b}A:@{ub} Paragondoors are supported by FAME. Use as Doortype '@{fg shine}TIM@{fg text}' and name the
   port '@{fg shine}DoorControl@{fg text}' (TIMDoorPort).
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} I'm @{b}programming@{ub} a new @{b}FAME-only door@{ub} and want to access some of FAME's
   Datafiles directly. When I read in the datas, I'll get wrong results out
   of the structures, but I'm using the @{u}NEWEST@{uu} includes !

@{b}A:@{ub} Don't forget to read in the structure header that every datafile of 
   FAME has! When reading structures, start at Offset @{fg shine}61@{fg text} instead of @{fg shine}0@{fg text} to
   skip the header.
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} What is the meaning of @{b}DoorHelp@{ub} ?

@{b}A:@{ub} It's a new online AmigaGuide Viewer which allows SysOps to use Amigaguide
   documentations as Online-Help for Doors. 

   As this door is not finished yet, this support is currently not available!
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} I can't find the @{b}conference accounting@{ub} Option. Where I could setup this
   Option ?

@{b}A:@{ub} Go into the internal UserEditor and load-in the User you want to change.
   Now go into the conference section (Press 'C') of the current usersettings
   and change the Conference Ratio from global to the ratio type you wish to
   setup for given conference and save this setting. Now repeat this step for
   all conferences you wish to have conference accounting set to on.
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} When @{b}using the FAMEFullEditor@{ub}, I can't save or use the extended commands
   with @{b}CTRL-S@{ub} or @{b}CTRL-Q@{ub}. Whenever I use this shortcuts, my Terminalprogram
   hangs and I have to restart the Terminal.

@{b}A:@{ub} You must enable the option "@{fg shine}Pass CTRL-S@{fg text} / @{fg shine}CTRL-Q@{fg text}" to allow your Terminal
   to send this controlcodes to FAME instead of interpreting them as commands!
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} When using the internal Shell, I'm getting the following error :
   "@{b}S:FAME-Startup not found !@{ub}" Also the usage of the screen seems to be not
   correct, I've setup @{b}57@{ub} lines to view but in FAME Shell I could only use
   @{b}6@{ub} lines.

@{b}A:@{ub} FAME's internal Shell uses a startup script similar to the original ADOS
   Shell, which uses the S:Shell-Startup file by default. This scriptfile
   will be used to setup the shell to your private needs. For FAME also such
   a file exists called @{fg shine}FAME-Startup@{fg text} and must be present in the @{fg shine}S:@{fg text} drawer.
   A sample FAME-Startup may look like :

   @{b}---@{ub} SNAP START @{b}---@{ub}

   Prompt "%N.%S> "
  
   @{b}---@{ub} SNAP  STOP @{b}---@{ub}

   Please look in your AmigaDos Manual for further informations about the
   shell startup scripts.
   To setup the right amount of lines to view you have to use command
   '@{fg shine}W 13 11@{fg text}'. Here you enter the amount of lines the shell should use. 
   Default setting is 6 lines to view.
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} Is it possible to make any @{b}input to the Spy Window@{ub} ?

@{b}A:@{ub} Yes, all you have to do is enabling the "@{fg shine}SpyWnd KeyInput@{fg text}" gadget found in
   SystemEditor->SystemDatas->MoreSystemDatas.
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} When I change some of the System/Conference Datas, FAME won't recognize
   this changings until I restart FAME !

@{b}A:@{ub} The autorecognition is currently under Development, future versions of FAME
   will support this feature, so all changings made will then automatically
   updated by FAME without restarting FAME.
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@endnode

@REM ==========================================================================

@node "FAQ_AMIEX" "Frequently asked Questions about AMIEX & FAME"

@{b}Q:@{ub} I'm @{b}changing from Amiex to FAME@{ub} and want to use some of the
   old Amiex doors under FAME, but they won't start or are displaying errors.

@{b}A:@{ub} Some of the Amiex icons are missing, the following icons are the most
   important ones: 
                        Icon       @{b}|@{ub}   Path to copy
                   @{b}----------------+------------------@{ub}
                   ConfConfig.info @{b}|@{ub} FAME:  
                   <CONFNAME>.info @{b}|@{ub} FAME:Conferences/
                          ACP.info @{b}|@{ub} Same dir like the FAME server.

   For some doors also the access icons (FAME:Access) are required. To 
   avoid problems, configure FAME to your personal wishes, including
   conference accesses, levels, conferences and Nodes. After you've
   finished, use ByteAndi's CLI-Tool '@{b}MAKEICON@{ub}' to create all of the
   required Icons including the Tooltypes! Also check out the Doortype and
   set it to XIM for amiex Tools!!!
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub} I have installed an @{b}amiex door@{ub} correctly, @{b}but it won't start@{ub},
   and I'm sure that I've made no mistakes during the installation.

@{b}A:@{ub} Maybe you've forgotten to set the right Doorport name in the doorport-
   names settings. To emulate the Amiexport, enter @{fg shine}AEDoorPort@{fg text} in the
   XIMDoorPort field. Note that this name is case-sensitive!

   Another great problem some /X doors have is the fact that these doors
   access amiex datafiles (i.e. user.data etc.) directly without using the
   internal BBS functions. Those doors won't work under FAME because all of
   the datastructures are COMPLETLY different to amiex (better it is :). If
   you are a programmer and want to have your doors compatible with FAME,
   please use ONLY the internal functions of Amiex (like LoadAccount() etc)
   to access datas, therefor FAME will be able to convert it's data to the
   XIM format before passing them to your application. This way is of course
   not the way to write high-performance doors, but to avoid the rewriting
   of XIM doors, use only these functions !
@{b}___________________________________________________________________________@{ub}

@endnode

